Comment: I don't know how to play the opening, so i played with tempo.
Leaving the pawn unprotected, but with a rick up his sleeves.
Taking and not knowing the trick.
Defending but sadly, my position started getting worse.
He just keeps on attacking me!
My only defence with a good purpose.
If i take the pawn, it  would be terrible.
So i decided that if he takes the c pawn, i would develop my knight with tempo, if he takes the e pawn, i would attack the queen with Bxe6.
Now i'm winning! I'm going to win a pawn or mate on c1
And he esinged because i will put mate on c1 now.
